item.title: Will Smith Reveals Don't Say They're Married Anymore at the age of 52
item.dc:creator: AccessAdmin
item.content:encoded:
Will Smith and Jada Pinkett Smith are never, ever getting divorced.
In a recent interview on TIDAL’s Rap Radar podcast, the 49-year-old rapper revealed that he and his wife have started to use an even more poignant word than “married” when referring to their relationship: “life partners.”
“We don’t even say we’re married anymore. We refer to ourselves as life partners, where you get into that space where you realize you are literally with somebody for the rest of your life,” Smith shared on the podcast. “There’s no deal breakers. There’s nothing she could do — ever. Nothing that would break our relationship. She has my support till death and it feels so good to get to that space.”

In the absence of Kate Middleton and Meghan Markle at a service at St Paul’s Cathedral today, fortunately actress Angelina Jolie was able to pick up the slack when it came to rocking a seriously dazzling regal ensemble. Attending the Service of Commemoration and Dedication of the Most Distinguished Order of St Michael and St George at the Cathedral, the 43-year-old looked chic in a dove grey cowl neck Ralph & Russo gown with a ruffled waist.She teamed the look with a golden bejewelled brooch, pearl earrings, matching gloves, and a hat topped with a ribbon. Meanwhile, her long brunette locks were tied neatly into a chignon. The star joined the congregation for the service marking the Order’s 200th anniversary and was later filmed practicing a royal-inspired wave to fans waiting outside. In the image, both models wear flashy silver sequin styles — Paloma is low-key chilling in a pool in a short sleeved, bateau-neck number, and Ashley is lounging nearby in a form-fitting piece topped with a shaggy gray sweater. This is apparently Vogue Arabia's "Body Revolution" issue, in which they declare that inside you'll find "The best summer looks to celebrate all shapes." Along with their twinning image, each woman has her own, close-up cover-shot as well, and they are both SERV-ING, y'all. Inside the mag, we hear from Ashley, who says making people comfortable with themselves has always been her calling: "My mother told me that when I walked into a room, I would greet every single person — even at three years old. It was more of an emotion that I would give people, and it would leave them feeling good about who they are," she said. "I think that's what I'm doing today: letting women know that they are worthy, that they are beautiful, and that they can be happy with who they are in their skin." Paloma talks about self-acceptance. "The feelings that I have about my body today aren't very different from the way I felt about it in first grade," she said. "What has changed is the way I navigate those feelings." This isn't the first Vogue rodeo for either lady. Ashley Graham has appeared on both American (in a group image) and British (solo) publications, while Paloma covered the May 2018 issue of British Vogue with other models who are "changing the face of fashion."

item.title: Kendall and Khloe had a pool party
item.dc:creator: AccessAdmin
item.content:encoded:
We need to talk about the Kardashians and their obsession with cycling fashion. It started and it should have ended with Kim Kardashian and her cycling shorts, but thanks to Kanye West, the Kardashians are now wearing so much spandex they look like they should be whizzing around a velodrome, not Calabasas California.
Khloe Kardashian has been having some much-needed sister time after moving back to LA with baby True and boyfriend Tristan Thompson. To celebrate the 4th of July, Kendall and Khloe had a pool party and Khloe wasted no time in channelling her inner Chris Hoy and throwing on some Yeezy Season 7 spandex, as Kendall shared on her Instagram Stories. I mean, it’s a look I’ll give her that but unless Khloe’s about to jump on a road bike and pedal for her life I think it’s one best left to the cycling professionals.

item.dc:creator: AccessAdmin
item.content:encoded:
hough her hips have never lied, even superstar bodies need some help to get into tip-top shape for the type of rigorous performing required for a massive world tour. This was certainly the case with Spanish music sensation Shakira.

These specific workouts started four months prior to the kick off of her tour. They were targeted to building up her endurance so that she could sustain performing for such a long period of time without sounding out of breath or losing her stamina. There was also a focus on her strength as she plays many instruments during the course of the 2-hour show. Shakira is a mother of 2 young boys, Milan, 5 and Sasha, 3, so she knows what it’s like to run around after little ones.

item.title: David and Victoria Beckham celebrate anniversary amid split speculation
item.dc:creator: AccessAdmin
item.content:encoded:
The superstar couple celebrated their 19th wedding anniversary Wednesday in Paris and made sure the world knew about it by posting on social media.

Teaming up with Her Royal Highness for their second engagement together in less than two weeks, Meghan Markle looked stunning as she attended a star-studded reception in honour of Queen Elizabeth II's Young Leaders Awards.For the glamorous occasion, the Duchess of Sussex looked chic in a light pink Prada dress which featured a double-breasted blouse and skirt complete with a matching belt. The look was similar to the Carolina Herrera off-the-shoulder-dress she wore for Trooping the Colour earlier this month. She teamed her look with a Prada leather clutch, black suede heels by Aquazzura Deneuve and her signature diamond cross bracelet by Vanessa Tugendhaft. The Queen hosted the annual ceremony at Buckingham Palace, which recognises the achievements of change-makers across the UK, and saw the likes of David Beckham, Sir Lenny Henry and ELLE cover star model Neelam Gill in attendance. During the celebrations, Prince Harry, who was recently named an ambassador of the organisation, addressed the 61 honorees with a heartwarming speech about their contributions to their communities.

item.title: Celebrity long-term couples who never married
item.dc:creator: AccessAdmin
item.content:encoded:
Heralding the official return of seriously big hair was model Kaia Gerber who stormed the Valentino AW18 couture runway with a bouffant large enough to rival Marie Antoinette.

Sashaying her way down the catwalk at the Hotel Rothschild in front of a celeb filled FROW complete with Tracee Ellis Ross, the model ingenue topped her candyfloss pink feather ball gown with astonishingly large hair.

Created by backstage legend and fashion industry face, hairstylist Guido Palau, the OTT look was all about more is more height and XXL extensions.Palau nonchalantly described the gravity-defying style as 'big hair', using wigs dyed to colour match the model's own hair by Josh Wood to create the 60s-inspired hairstyle.

Although just seven of the models were adorned with the outrageous wigs, the amount of work that went into them is remarkable.

Wood took to Instagram to break down the intricate process that went into creating the ginormous hair, which included no less than '50 wigs, 3700 miles, 250 colour processes, 150 hours of prep, 11 team members, 7 models and one inspiration'. So not much.

Kaia's prescribed hair colour? 'Dark chocolate bourbon-y base, with soft rich tea ends.'

Adding a Barbarella-esque extravagance to a collection filled with gold-trimmed capes, garish baroque prints and more maribou than Ru Paul's dressing room, if there was a way to out extra couture week, Valentino just did it.

In a recent interview on TIDAL’s Rap Radar podcast, the 49-year-old rapper revealed that he and his wife have started to use an even more poignant word than “married” when referring to their relationship: “life partners.”
“We don’t even say we’re married anymore. We refer to ourselves as life partners, where you get into that space where you realize you are literally with somebody for the rest of your life,” Smith shared on the podcast. “There’s no deal breakers. There’s nothing she could do — ever. Nothing that would break our relationship. She has my support till death and it feels so good to get to that space.”

item.title: Blake Shelton knows how to show his girlfriend he cares
item.dc:creator: AccessAdmin
item.content:encoded:
Blake Shelton knows how to show his girlfriend he cares.The 42-year-old country crooner took to Twitter on Monday to share what makes him a dedicated boyfriend to Gwen Stefani, who just began her Las Vegas residency last week.
“So far @gwenstefani has performed 3 shows in Las Vegas. I have been to 3... #stalker,” Shelton quipped. The pair, who have been together since 2015 after meeting on The Voice, are not shy about expressing their love for each other on social media. To celebrate her first show, the “Hollaback Girl” singer shared some sweet moments with her beau, including kissing pics and bouquet with a sweet note that Shelton sent ahead of his girlfriend's first show.
ET caught up with Stefani following her inaugural Vegas performance, and she chatted all about her relationship, including what Shelton knew about the show before he saw it.
“He’s, like, my bestie,” Stefani told ET’s Keltie Knight of her guy. “So, of course he’s seen everything as its been going and just bouncing off of him and stuff like that.”
Though Shelton knew a lot about 48-year-old pop star's show going in, the final moments — where she struts on stage in a tiny cowgirl outfit — were a surprise to him. The former No Doubt member even called wearing the outfit in front of Shelton “a fantasy” while she was on stage.
While the two are clearly smitten, Stefani admits she still has no immediate plans to move into the married phase. “I don’t know! I don’t have a future,” she said of a marriage timeline. “All I know is that I have a lot to look forward to.”

item.title: Every One Of Kaia Gerber's High-Fashion And Effortlessly Cool Looks
item.dc:creator: AccessAdmin
item.content:encoded:
There were many history-defining catwalk moments during SS17 Fashion Month.
A sense of feel-good nostalgia, frivolity and joy graced the runways, thanks to throwback 80s trends - stonewashed denim and shoulder pads - seen at the like of Stella McCartney, Isabel Marant and Givenchy.
And while the season's most iconic show might have been the return of the original Supermodels - with the likes of Carla Bruni, Naomi Campbell and Claudia Schiffer storming the runway at Versace in Milan - there was also a clear nod to the future, most notably with the help of Cindy Crawford's daughter, Kaia Gerber.
Kaia Gerber has been dubbed by fashion editors worldwide as the 'baby supermodel' to watch.This season, the 16-year-old made her catwalk debut, walking for the likes of Saint Laurent, Fendi, Miu Miu, Prada, Moschino and Alexander Wang to name but a few.
With her mother's killer figure, perfectly-sculpted brows, brilliant bone structure and olive-hued skin, Gerber was the sheer embodiment of fashion's wistful affection for the past but also, it's vision of the future.
Kaia is the daughter of model-turned-businessman Rande Gerber and 80s/90s supermodel Cindy Crawford. When she was just 10-years-old, she landed her first modelling gig for Versace's junior line, Young Versace. The star then went on to sign a modelling contract with IMG Models at the age of 13 - three years ahead of her mum who signed with Elite aged 16 - and made her first solo magazine cover for LOVE (shot by Kendall Jenner) when she was 14-year-old.

As a Beauty Editor I try a lottt of skincare products, every day a new face cream or serum lands on my desk and each one promises to transform my skin, blitz wrinkles, and banish breakouts. Nine times out of ten, it's just a jar full of marketing and empty promises. Sad, but true.
That's why I'm always fascinated by the skincare products people go back to time and time again, for a moisturiser or serum to earn loyalty it has to be a winner. With that in mind I decided to reach out to one of the UK's biggest beauty retailers, FeelUnique, to find out which - out of the 1000's of skincare products they sell - are the most popular, the ones they struggle to keep in stock. Intrigued? Here are they are...The 9 best-selling skincare products.
At number 8, this face mask has built up a serious following thanks to it's skin-smoothing powers. The clever formula helps to improve skin density - which can help the complexion look plump and glowy. Reviewers say it makes an 'instant difference', leaving skin looking 'younger and healthier' after the first use.
When it comes to the best eye cream, we've tried some of the finest formulas out there, but this is one we always come back to - and it appears the internet agrees with us. Yup, Filorga's Optim-Eyes was the best-selling eye cream on FeelUnique this past year, and came in at number 6 on the skincare best-seller list. The hyaluronic acid formula works a treat for giving dry, dull, tired eyes a shot of hydration.

With that in mind I decided to reach out to one of the UK's biggest beauty retailers, FeelUnique, to find out which - out of the 1000's of skincare products they sell - are the most popular, the ones they struggle to keep in stock. Intrigued? Here are they are...The 9 best-selling skincare products.
At number 8, this face mask has built up a serious following thanks to it's skin-smoothing powers. The clever formula helps to improve skin density - which can help the complexion look plump and glowy. Reviewers say it makes an 'instant difference', leaving skin looking 'younger and healthier' after the first use.
When it comes to the best eye cream, we've tried some of the finest formulas out there, but this is one we always come back to - and it appears the internet agrees with us. Yup, Filorga's Optim-Eyes was the best-selling eye cream on FeelUnique this past year, and came in at number 6 on the skincare best-seller list. The hyaluronic acid formula works a treat for giving dry, dull, tired eyes a shot of hydration.

item.content:encoded:
Attending the Service of Commemoration and Dedication of the Most Distinguished Order of St Michael and St George at the Cathedral, the 43-year-old looked chic in a dove grey cowl neck Ralph & Russo gown with a ruffled waist. She teamed the look with a golden bejewelled brooch, pearl earrings, matching gloves, and a hat topped with a ribbon. Meanwhile, her long brunette locks were tied neatly into a chignon.
Jolie was invited following her honorary damehood in 2014 for services to UK foreign policy and dedication to end sexual violence in war zones.
For her audience with the Queen that year, the Maleficent star wore a similar-coloured outfit by Ralph & Russo.
Speaking about her recognition at the time, Jolie said:
‘To receive an honour related to foreign policy means a great deal to me, as it is what I wish to dedicate my working life to. Working on PVSI and with survivors of rape is an honour in itself. I know that succeeding in our goals will take a lifetime, and I am dedicated to it for all of mine.’ Prince Edward, the Duke of Kent, stood in to represent the Queen who was forced to cancel due to ‘feeling under the weather’, Buckingham Palace confirmed today.
However, royal correspondent Rebecca English has assured royal fans that 'there is no cause for alarm', and that Her Majesty will be going to Windsor this afternoon as planned.In the absence of Kate Middleton and Meghan Markle at a service at St Paul's Cathedral today, fortunately actress Angelina Jolie was able to pick up the slack when it came to rocking a seriously dazzling regal ensemble.
